      "review_id": "BylH3HnQnm",
      "sentence_index": 0,
      "text": "The paper introduces a new approach to combine small RBMs that are pretrained in order to obtain a large RBM with good performance.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_structuring",
      "fine": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "asp": "none",
      "pol": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "BylH3HnQnm",
      "sentence_index": 1,
      "text": "This will bypass the need of training large RBMs and suggests to break them into smaller ones.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_structuring",
      "fine": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "asp": "none",
      "pol": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "BylH3HnQnm",
      "sentence_index": 2,
      "text": "The paper then provides experimental evidence by applying the method on \"invertible boolean logic\".",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_structuring",
      "fine": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "asp": "none",
      "pol": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "BylH3HnQnm",
      "sentence_index": 3,
      "text": "MCMC is used to find the the solution to large RBM and compare it against the combined solutions of smaller RBMs.",
      "suffix": "\n\n\n",
      "coarse": "arg_structuring",
      "fine": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "asp": "none",
      "pol": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "BylH3HnQnm",
      "sentence_index": 4,
      "text": "The paper motivates the problem well, however, it is not well-written and at times it is hard to follow.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_structuring",
      "fine": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "asp": "none",
      "pol": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "BylH3HnQnm",
      "sentence_index": 5,
      "text": "The details of the approach is not entirely clear and no theoritcal results are provided to support the approach.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_clarity",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "BylH3HnQnm",
      "sentence_index": 6,
      "text": "For instance, in the introduced approach, only an example of combination is provided in Figure 1.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "none",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "none",
      "pol": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "BylH3HnQnm",
      "sentence_index": 7,
      "text": "It is not clear how smaller RBMs (and their associated parameters) are combined to obtain the larger RBM model.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_clarity",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "BylH3HnQnm",
      "sentence_index": 8,
      "text": "From the experimental perspective, the experimental evidence on \"invertible boolean logic\" does not seem to be very convincing for validating the approach.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_soundness-correctness",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "BylH3HnQnm",
      "sentence_index": 9,
      "text": "Additionally, the details of the settings of the experiments are not fully discussed.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_substance",
      "pol": "pol_neutral"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "BylH3HnQnm",
      "sentence_index": 10,
      "text": "For example, what are the atomic/smaller problems and associated RBMs? what is the larger problem and how is the corresponding RBM obtained?",
