      "details": {}
    },
    {
      "review_id": "BylH3HnQnm",
      "rebuttal_id": "HJec4jK_R7",
      "sentence_index": 8,
      "text": "It has been shown in many texts that Gibbs Sampling converges to this equilibrium distribution at a geometric rate in Markov Random Fields.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "dispute",
      "fine": "rebuttal_mitigate-criticism",
      "alignment": [
        "context_sentences",
        [
          11
        ]
      ],
      "details": {}
    },
    {
      "review_id": "BylH3HnQnm",
      "rebuttal_id": "HJec4jK_R7",
      "sentence_index": 9,
      "text": "Finding the exact convergence rate involves calculation of the eigenstructure of the markov chain transition matrix, which is in general computationally intractable for RBMs of moderate size [1].",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "dispute",
      "fine": "rebuttal_mitigate-criticism",
      "alignment": [
        "context_sentences",
        [
          11
        ]
      ],
      "details": {}
    },
    {
      "review_id": "BylH3HnQnm",
      "rebuttal_id": "HJec4jK_R7",
      "sentence_index": 10,
      "text": "Given this, we have added an extra theorem to show how the upper bounds on convergence rate changes as we merge RBMs, this can be seen in Section 3.1 on \u201cConvergence Rate and MCMC\u201d.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "concur",
      "fine": "rebuttal_done",
      "alignment": [
        "context_sentences",
        [
          11
        ]
      ],
      "details": {
        "request_out_of_scope": true
